# PSL navigation-list strictness

When lowering PSL relation navigation list fields (for example `User.posts Post[]`) in `@prisma-next/sql-contract-psl`:

- Treat them as navigation-only metadata fields, never storage columns.
- Allow only `@relation` on navigation list fields.
- On navigation list fields, allow only relation name forms:
  - `@relation("Name")`
  - `@relation(name: "Name")`
- Reject `@relation(fields: ...)`, `@relation(references: ...)`, `onDelete`, and `onUpdate` on the list side.
- Reject all other attributes on navigation list fields as strict diagnostics.

This keeps PSL behavior fail-loud and avoids silently ignoring unsupported metadata.
